@node Customisable Variables
@section Customisable Variables

Kasten is customisable using @samp{customize}, via @kbd{M-x customize-group @key{RET} kasten @key{RET}}. Alternatively, one may use @code{setq}.  For
example, to change the variable @samp{kasten-directory} to @samp{~/notes} using @code{setq},
one may add the following code to their Emacs configuration file (such as
@samp{init.el}, preferably under @samp{use-package}).

@lisp
(setq kasten-directory (expand-file-name "~/notes/"))
@end lisp

Default values in the manual may be evaluated, simplified or slightly modified.
Please refer to the source code and search for @samp{defcustom}.


@defvar kasten-directory
Note directory.

Default value: @samp{~/jrn/}.
@end defvar

@defvar kasten-file-extensions
List of searchable file extensions for Kasten.

Default value: @samp{("org" "txt" "tex")}.
@end defvar

@defvar kasten-default-extension
Default extension for new notes.

Default value: @samp{org}.
@end defvar

